Please fix word wrap in this commit message to prevent the line length issues.
Couple of minor nits to fix.
How the logging is handled for bic console ?  how the logging is handled if we switch console b/w host and bic ?

For each server, a log file will be generated when BMC has booted, any data received from corresponding tty serial endpoint (e.g., ttyS0) will be logged into the file, when switching between host and bic, it only change the mux of the ttyS, so the log is mixed.
According to the suggestion from Michael, we divided the listening port of Host/BIC from 2200~2207 to 2200~2203/2300~2303, to provide more intuitive usage.
